OL,3,C'Racism normalised' say Teesside
OL,4,CMuslims after riots in Hartlepool
OL,6,FOne man told ITV News Tyne Tees his
OL,7,Fwife was "too scared" to leave the
OL,8,Fhouse this morning and another said
OL,9,F"racism is now normalised again".
OL,11,FAmjid Khazir, who runs Media Cultured,
OL,12,Fan organisation promoting social
OL,13,Fcohesion and inclusion by holding anti-
OL,14,Fracism and anti-radicalisation
OL,15,Fworkshops at schools, colleges, sports
OL,16,Fclubs and businesses, said it feels
OL,17,Flike a return to the "bad old days" of
OL,18,Fthe 80s.
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G2/9
